It was ok.  $16 for 2 tacos and some corn is pretty steep.  Especially since there was only 2 slices of tuna on each taco, the shell is mostly filled with slaw.  After spending $21, eating everything on my plate, I left hungry.  Might be a good place for drinks and munchies, but very overpriced for dinner.

I complained about my drink, and even after a watered down fix, I paid for my drink. However, I refused to tip well (because 1. I waited quite a while for it and 2. two other people tasted the drink and agreed it was really bad). When the bartender tried to take my drink away from me early, I told her that I wasn't done with it. She then threw the remainder of my drink in my face and told me to get out. (FYI, I consider that to be an assault / battery, outside of that fact that no one should ever be treated so rudely.) I will never come back here ever again, and I will never recommend that anyone ever come here.
Food is alright, drinks are stiff, staff is good. Good location for people downtown and open later than most other places. Way better than District.

Fantastic menu.   Not your typical bar fare.   More healthy options.  No deep fryer.   Free shots when the Blackhawks score!

Overall, completely unimpressed. The word "pub" is very misleading - as no burgers are sold here. The menu features very "hip" or "modern" options. Also, expensive. During my visit, I did enjoy pulled bacon french fries and a turkey chili - both were very delicious.

Stood there for 10 minutes (and even said excuse me TWICE) during stroll on state at the bar and the bar tender with the plaid hat on ignored us and served other people. Terrible service we had to walk out!
Slow service and expensive ($5 slice of pie for example). Disappointed with the "fancy menu".

Bartender/ owner, I guess she was the owner judging by her attitude, very rude, walk in the door she ask " can I help you?" I say, "are you closing?" Her reply "No" Bar had about 10 other people inside I had never been there before so she says " the kitchen is closed" "and again for the third time what can I get you" without offering  a drink menu or even giving a run down on the beverages sold there. Long story short, I will not be returning, this bartender was rude and the others seemed to be following suit. It seemed like her motive was to create an uneasiness so that we would leave, she tried to antagonize us to get a reaction from us by constantly being rude she let us know that we were not welcomed there. No cordial greeting or can I help you guys whatsoever. But she accomplished her goal with us deciding to leave the establishment. Blantant racism is very much a real thing in Rockford, Ill. If she was not the owner,  they should know what she's doing there. And if she's a manager her attitude is horrible along with the rest of the staff there. Seems like a nice place, but I wont be returning and I hope others avoid it as well. Horrible service, if you want to call it that.  *Avoid this establishment

A great choice for those attending downtown events.

Seriously. This food.   The drinks.  Why did I wait so long to try this menu?!?!   Thai the Chef made the most incredible butter baked cod I’ve ever had.  Drawn butter made this taste like lobster.  I can’t believe how heavenly this food was.   I’m already craving this again in my next week.   Tasha made a muddled Old Fashioned that took me back to the holidays with my grandparents.  It’s insanely old fashioned.  Muddled fresh orange.   Sweet.  Smokey. All the yes.
